== STATEMENT UNDER TEST ==
Conjecture 4.1 (arXiv:2601.03293): "For all integers n >= 2k+1,
the independence polynomial I(GP(n,k),x) has only real roots if
and only if k is even."  GP domain: n >= 3, 1 <= k < n/2.

GP(9,2): I = [1, 18, 126, 438, 801, 747, 303, 27]
  degree 7, squarefree=True, distinct real roots (Sturm, exact) = 5
  => NOT real-rooted although k=2 is even: the 'if' direction is FALSE.
  brute-force 2^18 subset enumeration: coefficients confirmed

GP(7,3): I = [1, 14, 70, 154, 147, 49]
  degree 5, squarefree=True, distinct real roots (Sturm, exact) = 5
  => real-rooted although k=3 is odd: the 'only if' direction is FALSE.
  brute-force 2^14 subset enumeration: coefficients confirmed
GP(3,1) (triangular prism): I = [1, 6, 6], real_rooted=True (k=1 odd)
  => second, minimal 'only if' violation (n=3 >= 2*1+1).

== STRUCTURAL INCOHERENCE: GP(7,2) ~= GP(7,3) ==
explicit isomorphism GP(7,2) -> GP(7,3):  u_j |-> v_{3j mod 7},  v_j |-> u_{3j mod 7}
  verified: bijection on 14 vertices; all 21 edges map bijectively onto all 21 edges.
  consistency: I(GP(7,2)) = I(GP(7,3)) = [1, 14, 70, 154, 147, 49]
  GP(7,2) has k even, GP(7,3) has k odd, yet they are the SAME graph:
  the conjecture's predicate is not isomorphism-invariant, so as
  stated it is not even well-posed (and with k=2 it predicts
  real-rooted for this graph, which is correct here, while with
  k=3 it predicts non-real-rooted for the very same graph).

